  "prompt": "Why does Enrique Iglesias always wear a cap when performing?",
  "response": "Enrique Iglesias has often been seen wearing a cap during his performances for several reasons. Some of these may include:\n\n1. **Personal Style**: A cap can be a part of his signature look and personal style, helping him stand out and create a recognizable image.\n\n2. **Comfort**: Performing can be physically demanding, and wearing a cap might provide him with extra comfort or help manage perspiration.\n\n3. **Visual Appeal**: A cap can add to the overall aesthetic of a performance and might enhance his connection with the audience.\n\n4. **Practicality**: Depending on the venue and lighting, a cap can help shield his eyes from bright stage lights.\n\n5. **Hair Management**: A cap can also be a way to manage his hairstyle, especially if he prefers a certain look or wants to avoid any distractions related to his hair during a performance.\n\nUltimately, the choice might be a combination of these factors and personal preference.",
